review_blob: Has a light hop aroma.  Huge frothy white head, transparent gold in color.  Taste is clean, lightly bitter, with an average finish.  Body is light, dry texture, soft carbonation.

Aroma is lightly sweet, some vanilla.  Appearance is very nice, light amber, kind of cloudy, with a frothy head.  Flavor is okay, kind of mild, and palate is lighter than I expected with lively carb and a somewhat watery texture.  I agree with the reviewer from Ohio who feels that this Sam Smith would be better in the summertime.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Organic Best Ale / Organically Produced Ale

review_blob: Aroma is very sweet and strong, as is flavor.. sweet with a nice long finish.  Its a beautiful dark brown with an awesome head.  Full body with great carbonation and a clean finish.

This one poured black with a small brown head and had a very appealing vanilla malt aroma.  The wonderful malt flavor and not too thick palate really impressed me.  The finish is nearly perfect, as is the carbonation and texture.

This had a great vanilla aroma and a gorgeous dark cider brown color to it, with a nice head.  It has a light bitterness to it with a shorter finish.  This one really goes down with ease, with a lighter body than what I expected and not too much carbonation.
Nice caramel, malt, coffee aroma.  Very dark with just a fleeting head.  Flavor is complex and rather bitter, with a long finish.  Body is medium, texture is dry, and carbonation is soft.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Citrus spice aroma, dark brown hue and nice initial head. Lighty sweet flavor with a shorter finish.  Nice light body and texture, not much carbonation.
Aroma is light and subtle, hue is appealing dark orange, frothy head.  Flavor is a bit bitter initially and finish is good.  Medium body, texture is dry, and carbonation is soft.

Grapefruit, spicy, floral aroma, with a moderately bitter flavor.  Pours dark golden brown with a small head.  Has a medium body, with somewhat soft carbonation.  Finish is long and smooth, and lightly alcoholic.
Wow, this really is spicy, a bit caramelly too.  Has a long finish and lasting head.
Maudite has such a handsome light brown hue to it, with a nice lasting head.  The carbonation is noticably lively, flavor is indeed complex, and the finish is full and smooth.  I like.
Pretty okay citrus aroma and flavor.  The texture and finish were just okay too.
This was a wonderful, full bodied, chocolatey stout, deep black with a lasting head.  Its pretty thick, with a lasting finish.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Really nice reddish ale with a pretty good head.  Citrus, nice lively carbonation, and a fine finish.

My Yeti poured jet black into the glass and really reminded me of coffee.  Looking at it, I expected a thicker beer, and was surprised by how thin it was in my mouth.  Also, the finish was strong enough for me to take note of the 9.5% alcohol.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged
